.TH ILF 1 "2025" "Immutable Linux Framework" "User Commands"
.
.SH NAME
ilf \- manage immutable Linux systems through a unified interface
.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ilf
[\fB\-\-config\fR \fIFILE\fR]
[\fB\-v\fR]
\fICOMMAND\fR [\fIARGS\fR]
.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ilf
is the command-line interface for the Immutable Linux Framework.
It provides a single, backend-agnostic surface for initialising,
upgrading, rolling back, and managing snapshots on immutable Linux systems.
.PP
The active backend is selected in
.I /etc/ilf/ilf.toml
under the
.B [ilf].backend
key.
All operations are dispatched through the Hardware Abstraction Layer (HAL)
to the configured backend.
.PP
Supported backends:
.RS
.TP
.B abroot
Vanilla-OS/ABRoot \(em A/B partition swap + OCI images
.TP
.B ashos
ashos/ashos \(em BTRFS snapshot tree
.TP
.B frzr
ChimeraOS/frzr \(em read-only BTRFS subvolume deploy
.TP
.B akshara
blend-os/akshara \(em YAML-declared system rebuild
.TP
.B btrfs-dwarfs
btrfs-dwarfs-framework \(em BTRFS+DwarFS hybrid blend layer
.TP
.B nixos
NixOS \(em generation-based passthrough
.RE
.
.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-\-config " FILE"
Path to the configuration file.
Defaults to the first file found in:
.IR $HOME/.config/ilf/ilf.toml ,
.IR /etc/ilf/ilf.toml ,
.IR /usr/share/ilf/ilf.toml ,
.IR ./ilf.toml .
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Enable verbose output.
.
.SH COMMANDS
.
.SS ilf init
.B ilf init
[\fB\-\-distro\fR \fINAME\fR]
[\fB\-\-backend\fR \fINAME\fR]
[\fB\-\-arch\fR \fIARCH\fR]
[\fB\-\-disk\fR \fIDEVICE\fR]
[\fB\-\-efi\fR]
[\fB\-\-encrypt\fR]
[\fB\-\-extra-subvols\fR \fILIST\fR]
.PP
Initialise ILF on this system.
When
.B \-\-disk
is provided, the target disk is partitioned, formatted, and the BTRFS
subvolume layout for the chosen backend is created under
.IR /mnt .
The backend's own
.B Init()
routine is then called to complete setup.
.PP
When
.B \-\-disk
is omitted, only the backend
.B Init()
is run.
This is useful when the disk is already partitioned by a live installer.
.TP
.BI \-\-distro " NAME"
Target distro identifier (e.g.\&
.IR arch ,
.IR debian ,
.IR fedora ).
Must match a file in
.IR /etc/ilf/distros/<NAME>.toml .
.TP
.BI \-\-backend " NAME"
Immutability backend to use.
Overrides
.B [ilf].backend
in the config file.
.TP
.BI \-\-arch " ARCH"
Target CPU architecture.
Auto-detected if omitted.
Valid values:
.IR x86_64 ,
.IR aarch64 ,
.IR armv7 ,
.IR riscv64 ,
.IR ppc64le ,
.IR s390x .
.TP
.BI \-\-disk " DEVICE"
Block device to partition (e.g.\&
.IR /dev/sda ,
.IR /dev/nvme0n1 ).
.B Warning:
all existing data on this device will be destroyed.
.TP
.B \-\-efi
Create an EFI System Partition.
Enabled by default.
Disable with
.B \-\-efi=false
for BIOS/legacy boot.
.TP
.B \-\-encrypt
Encrypt the root partition with LUKS2.
.TP
.BI \-\-extra-subvols " LIST"
Comma-separated list of additional BTRFS subvolumes to create beyond the
backend defaults (e.g.\&
.IR @snapshots,@opt ).
.
.SS ilf upgrade
.B ilf upgrade
[\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR]
[\fB\-\-force\fR]
[\fB\-\-pkg\fR \fIPKG\fR[,\fIPKG\fR...]]
.PP
Perform an atomic system upgrade.
Before upgrading, a pre-upgrade snapshot is created automatically.
If the upgrade fails and
.B auto_rollback
is enabled in
.IR ilf.toml ,
the system is rolled back to the pre-upgrade snapshot.
Pre- and post-upgrade hooks are run if configured.
.TP
.B \-\-dry\-run
Report what would change without applying it.
.TP
.B \-\-force
Skip pre-flight checks.
.TP
.BI \-\-pkg " PKG"
Additional packages to install during the upgrade.
May be specified multiple times or as a comma-separated list.
.
.SS ilf rollback
.B ilf rollback
[\fB\-\-snapshot\fR \fIID\fR]
.PP
Revert the system to the previous state.
If
.B \-\-snapshot
is omitted, the backend chooses the most recent previous state.
.TP
.BI \-\-snapshot " ID"
Specific snapshot ID to roll back to.
.
.SS ilf snapshot
.B ilf snapshot
.IR SUBCOMMAND " [" OPTIONS ]
.PP
Manage snapshots.
.TP
.B ilf snapshot create [\-\-label LABEL]
Create a snapshot of the current root.
The snapshot is named
.IB LABEL - TIMESTAMP
where
.I TIMESTAMP
is in ISO 8601 format.
Prints the backend-assigned snapshot ID on success.
.TP
.B ilf snapshot list
List all snapshots.
The currently deployed snapshot is marked with
.BR * .
.TP
.B ilf snapshot delete \-\-id ID
Delete the snapshot with the given ID.
Deployed snapshots are never deleted.
.TP
.B ilf snapshot deploy \-\-id ID
Set the snapshot with the given ID as the next boot target.
.
.SS ilf status
.B ilf status
.PP
Display the current system state: active backend, current root,
mutability, snapshot count, and any backend-specific metadata.
.
.SS ilf mutable
.B ilf mutable
.IR SUBCOMMAND
.PP
Toggle filesystem mutability.
.TP
.B ilf mutable enter
Make the root filesystem temporarily writable.
The active session is recorded in
.I /run/ilf-mutable.lock
so that
.B ilf mutable exit
can restore immutability from a separate process.
.TP
.B ilf mutable exit
Restore immutability by reading
.I /run/ilf-mutable.lock
and reversing the toggle method used during
.BR enter .
Returns an error if no session is active.
.
.SS ilf pkg
.B ilf pkg
.IR SUBCOMMAND " " PACKAGE ...
.PP
Manage packages inside an atomic transaction.
Not all backends support this operation; see
.B ilf backends
for capability information.
.TP
.B ilf pkg add PACKAGE...
Install one or more packages atomically.
.TP
.B ilf pkg remove PACKAGE...
Remove one or more packages atomically.
.
.SS ilf backends
.B ilf backends
.PP
List all registered backends and their capability flags.
.PP
Capability flags:
.RS
.TP
.B snapshot
Named snapshot create/list/delete/deploy
.TP
.B rollback
Revert to previous state
.TP
.B atomic-pkg
Per-package install/remove in a transaction
.TP
.B oci-images
Pull and apply OCI container images
.TP
.B mutable
Toggle read-write mode at runtime
.TP
.B compression
Backend-native data compression
.TP
.B multi-boot
Manage multiple bootable entries
.TP
.B thin-provision
LVM thin provisioning support
.RE
.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/ilf/ilf.toml
System-wide configuration file.
See
.BR ilf.toml (5)
for the full schema.
.TP
.I /etc/ilf/distros/*.toml
Per-distro capability declarations.
.TP
.I /run/ilf-mutable.lock
Active mutable session token.
Created by
.B ilf mutable enter
and removed by
.BR "ilf mutable exit" .
.TP
.I /usr/lib/systemd/system/ilf-update.service
Systemd service unit for periodic upgrades.
.TP
.I /usr/lib/systemd/system/ilf-update.timer
Systemd timer that triggers
.I ilf-update.service
daily with a randomised delay.
.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Initialise a new system on
.I /dev/nvme0n1
using the
.B ashos
backend on Arch Linux:
.PP
.RS
.EX
ilf init \-\-distro arch \-\-backend ashos \-\-disk /dev/nvme0n1 \-\-efi
.EE
.RE
.PP
Perform a dry-run upgrade to see what would change:
.PP
.RS
.EX
ilf upgrade \-\-dry\-run
.EE
.RE
.PP
Create a named snapshot before making manual changes:
.PP
.RS
.EX
ilf snapshot create \-\-label before\-experiment
.EE
.RE
.PP
Make the root temporarily writable, install a package, then restore:
.PP
.RS
.EX
ilf mutable enter
pacman \-S --noconfirm htop
ilf mutable exit
.EE
.RE
.PP
Roll back to a specific snapshot:
.PP
.RS
.EX
ilf rollback \-\-snapshot 20250101T120000Z
.EE
.RE
.PP
List all registered backends and their capabilities:
.PP
.RS
.EX
ilf backends
.EE
.RE
.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
An error occurred.
The error message is printed to stderr.
.
